The fountain dome is about 18 meters across. Since the Sun is 77,333,000 times larger than that, to make this model, we shrink all sizes and distances by that same amount. That makes Mars the size of a tangerine, right here, going at the pace of a tiny snail, around Lake Eola.
The speed of light, the fastest anything can happen in space, is as fast as you can sprint.
Find more information on the web at eolasun.info/mars
